<!-- Title Tag -->
<title>Demonstrating Basic HTML Tags in WordPress</title>

<!-- Main Heading -->
<h1>Welcome to My HTML Tags Demo Blog</h1>

<!-- Paragraph -->
<p>This blog demonstrates how different HTML tags work when used inside WordPress. These tags are essential for structuring webpages and adding meaning to the content.</p>

<!-- Subheading -->
<h2>1. Paragraph and Heading Tags</h2>
<p>The <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> to <code>&lt;h6&gt;</code> tags define headings, and the <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> tag defines paragraphs.</p>
<h3>This is an H3 heading</h3>
<p>This is a normal paragraph written using the <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> tag.</p>

<!-- Anchor Tag -->
<h2>2. Anchor Tag (Hyperlink)</h2>
<p>You can create clickable links using the <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> tag.</p>
<p>Example: Visit 
   <a href="https://www.wordpress.org" target="_blank">WordPress Official Website</a>.
</p>

<!-- Text Formatting -->
<h2>3. Text Formatting Tags</h2>
<p><b>This text is bold.</b></p>
<p><i>This text is italic.</i></p>
<p><u>This text is underlined.</u></p>

<!-- Image Tag -->
<h2>4. Image Tag</h2>
<p>You can add images using the <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> tag.</p>
<img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/9a/WordPress_blue_logo.svg" width="120" alt="WordPress Logo">

<!-- Closing -->
<h2>Conclusion</h2>
<p>We successfully demonstrated the usage of <code>&lt;title&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;a&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> to <code>&lt;h3&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;p&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;b&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;i&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;u&gt;</code>, and <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> tags inside a WordPress blog post.</p>
